\c 79
\s1 Mazmur yang ditulis oleh Asaf
\q1
\v 1 Ya, Allah, suku-suku yang tidak mengenal Engkau sudah menyerang negeri yang Engkau berikan kepada umat-Mu.
\q2 Dan mereka sudah membuat Rumah-Mu menjadi najis,
\q1 dan menghancurkan semua bangunan-bangunan yang ada di Yerusalem.
\q1
\v 2 \add Bukannya menguburkan \add*mayat-mayat umat-Mu yang \add mereka bunuh,\add*
\q2 mereka biarkan mayat-mayat itu menjadi makanan burung pemakan bangkai,
\q2 dan hewan buas lainnya.
\q1
\v 3 Ketika mereka membunuh umat-Mu,
\q1 darah mereka mengalir seperti air melalui \add jalan-jalan \add*Yerusalem,
\q2 dan \add hampir\add* saja tidak ada satu orangpun yang masih hidup untuk menguburkan mayat-mayat mereka.
\q1
\v 4 Bangsa-bangsa lain yang tinggal di sekeliling negeri kami menghina kami,
\q2 kami menjadi bahan olokan dan ejekan bagi mereka.
\b
\q1
\v 5 Ya TUHAN, berapa lama \add lagi hal ini akan terus seperti ini?\add*
\q2 Apakah untuk selamanya Engkau marah kepada kami?
\q1 Will your being angry be like a fire burning \add within you\add*?
\q1
\v 6 \add Instead of being angry with us\add*,
\q2 be angry with the people-groups that do not know/worship you!
\q1 Be angry with kingdoms whose people do not pray to you,
\q2
\v 7 because they have killed Israeli people
\q2 and they have ruined your country.
\q1
\v 8 Do not punish us because of the sins that our ancestors committed!
\q1 Act mercifully toward us now/quickly,
\q2 because we are very discouraged.
\b
\q1
\v 9 God, you have saved/rescued \add us many times\add*,
\q2 so help us \add now\add*;
\q1 rescue us and forgive us for having sinned
\q2 in order that other people will honor you [MTY].
\q1
\v 10 It is not right that [RHQ] the other people-groups say \add aboutus\add*,
\q2 “If their God \add is very powerful\add*, why does he not \add helpthem\add*?”
\q1 Allow us to see you punishing the people of other nations in return for their shedding our blood
\q1 and killing many of us, your people.
\q1
\v 11 Listen to your people groaning while they are in prison,
\q2 and by your great power free those whom our enemies say that they will certainly execute.
\b
\q1
\v 12 In return for their having often insulted you,
\q1 punish them seven times as much!
\q1
\v 13 After you do that, we, whom you \add take care of like a shepherd takes careof\add* his sheep, will continue praising you;
\q2 we will continue to praise you forever [HYP].